description.p:
According to a first aspect of the embodiments of the present invention, a headphone socket assembly is provided. The headphone socket assembly may include: a headphone socket and an electromagnetic shield device;

the headphone socket is electrically connected to a circuit board in an electronic equipment; and

the electromagnetic shield device is disposed at a periphery of the headphone socket.

Optionally, the headphone socket assembly further includes a connector;

pins of the headphone socket are electrically connected to a conductive track on the circuit board via the connector;

the electromagnetic shield device is an electromagnetic shielding layer which covers the periphery of the headphone socket.

According to a second aspect of the embodiments of the present invention, an electronic equipment is provided. The electronic equipment includes: a headphone socket assembly and a circuit board;

the headphone socket assembly includes a headphone socket and an electromagnetic shield device;

the headphone socket is electrically connected to the circuit board in the electronic equipment; and

the electromagnetic shield device is disposed at a periphery of the headphone socket.

Optionally, the headphone socket assembly further includes a connector;

pins of the headphone socket are electrically connected to a conductive track on the circuit board via the connector;

the electromagnetic shield device is an electromagnetic shielding layer which covers the periphery of the headphone socket.

claim.claim-text:
The headphone socket assembly according to claim 1, characterized in that the headphone socket assembly further comprises a connector (304);

pins of the headphone socket are electrically connected to a conductive track on the circuit board via the connector (304);

the electromagnetic shield device is an electromagnetic shielding layer which covers the periphery of the headphone socket.

An electronic equipment (400,500,600), characterized in that the electronic equipment comprises: a headphone socket assembly (410,510,610) and a circuit board (420,520,620);

the headphone socket assembly (410,510,610) comprises a headphone socket (411,511,611) and an electromagnetic shield device (412,512,612);

the headphone socket is electrically connected to the circuit board in the electronic equipment; and

the electromagnetic shield device is disposed at a periphery of the headphone socket.

The electronic equipment according to claim 6, characterized in that the headphone socket assembly further comprises a connector (613);

pins of the headphone socket are electrically connected to a conductive track on the circuit board via the connector;

the electromagnetic shield device is an electromagnetic shielding layer which covers the periphery of the headphone socket.
